Yes, the production sent us videos of several groups and this band liked us best. Therefore, we are curious to see what Las Robertas can offer live. This is sure to be exciting.
Why do you always change the text of Yellow Ledbetter when you play live?
This is a question for Ed (Eddie Vedder), I have no idea.
He sings him, and I think he sings the first thing in his heart.
Who were you influenced by as a bassist?
Of so many+
The first ones that impress me include Geezer Butler, John Entwistle, C. J. Ramone, John Doe, Paul McCartney, Chuck Dukowski...
There are so many that I could talk all afternoon about the bassists I liked.
How has Pearl Jam managed to keep the grunge alive, even though it is no longer a fashion show?
I don't think we all feel very attached to the word grunge.
When I think about it, I think about the bands that I mentioned before, such as Mudhoney, Soundgarden, Nirvana and all the others that came up at the same time. If they are still important today, I find it great because it is worth listening to this music and bands like Mudhoney now make better music than ever before.
At first, her music was darker, now she's more positive.
Why?
This is interesting because I think there are a few songs on the new album that might seem a bit easy. But there are also other songs like The End or Just Breathe that are rated as very dark songs, although they also have something positive in themselves.
Both came to me the tears when I heard Ed playing them. They are very dark songs.
I believe that if you get older and something traumatic happened in your life - for example, if you lose a family member or a friend - it affects your artistic work and your music and these two songs clearly embodies this for me.
But I also believe that you can be a happy person and still make dark music.
