Fujimori came back to the hospital for medical examinations
Former President Alberto Fujimori was sent to a public hospital on Tuesday to investigate the muscle loss of his legs, informed his home doctor.
The 72-year-old Fujimori, who has been detained for 25 years for violations of human rights during his reign (1990-2000), has several diseases, including tongue cancer, which is operated four times and under control.
Alejandro Aguinaga, congress member and his personal doctor, told TV that Fujimori would be examined for three days in the Peruvian hospital Instituto Nacional de Enfermedades Neoplásicas to determine the reason for his pain and muscle loss in the lower limbs.
Aguinaga commented that he felt that Fujimori could be pardoned for humanitarian reasons, and yet he did not wish to do so because he thought he was innocent.
He was operated on tongue cancer four times and he lost 18 kilograms of weight. In addition, other diseases such as severe erosive gastritis, a cyst in the pancreas, kidney stones, high blood pressure and bleeding problems in the legs were listed by the doctor.
Fujimori has been located in Dirección Nacional de Operaciones Especiales de la policía since September 2007.
In April 2009, he was sentenced to 25 years in prison for the murder of 25 people by the death squad of the Peruvian army, which was secretly active during his reign.
