An official decree, led by the Uuguay president José Mujica, consisting of several ministers and entrepreneurs, will start their visit to Mexico on Tuesday to expand trade between both countries and discuss political issues in the region
Mujica will meet with his Mexican counterpart Felipe Calderón next Wednesday. According to the Uuguay president, this will be the culmination of his booked schedule with politicians, businessmen and a meeting with the collection of Uruguayians living in Mexico.
