In addition, he said that no helicopter parts were found during the investigations in the area on which the machine had come down.
"When searching no aircraft parts were found elsewhere, the impact was on the entire structure.
The helicopter was built for 19 inmates, so he met all the conditions for passenger transport.
The area has a slope of 7 to 30 degrees.
At present, it is a priority to obtain the results of the investigation as soon as possible, but these could take several months, perhaps even a year.
